              {
                "description": "<p>Specifies the condition of a file transfer protocol-enabled server for the server that was described. A value of <code>ONLINE</code> indicates that the server can accept jobs and transfer files. A <code>State</code> value of <code>OFFLINE</code> means that the server cannot perform file transfer operations.</p> <p>The states of <code>STARTING</code> and <code>STOPPING</code> indicate that the server is in an intermediate state, either not fully able to respond, or not fully offline. The values of <code>START_FAILED</code> or <code>STOP_FAILED</code> can indicate an error condition.</p>"
